"version": "1.0.2",
"title": "8326: purity, moral and spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8326: purity, moral and spiritual",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Moral and spiritual purity is demanded by God of his people. God calls his people to be holy, just as he is holy.</p>\n<h2>Divine purity</h2>\n<h3>The purity of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:17\">JOB 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:26\">PSA 18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:5\">1JN 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The purity of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:3\">1JN 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h2>Fellowship with God demands purity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:3-Ps24:4\">PSA 24:3–24:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:6\">PSA 51:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:1\">PSA 73:1</a></p>\n<h2>God's people are to live pure lives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:30\">LEV 18:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:1\">JOB 31:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7-1Cor5:8\">1CO 5:7–5:8</a> <em>Yeast is a symbol of sin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:15-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:15–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3\">1TH 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:15\">TIT 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:5\">TIT 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:8\">JAS 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Purity is unobtainable by human effort</h2>\n<h3>Because of the sinful human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:4\">JOB 14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:14\">JOB 15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:4\">JOB 25:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:20\">ECC 7:20</a></p>\n<h3>Because of the tendency to idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:5\">HOS 8:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Because of self-deception</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:12\">PRO 30:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:9\">PRO 20:9</a></p>\n<h3>Because of an unwillingness to be cleansed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:13\">EZK 24:13</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Symbols of purification from sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7\">PSA 51:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:6\">ISA 6:6</a> <em>fire</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:4\">MRK 1:4</a> <em>water baptism</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:2\">2CO 11:2</a> <em>virginity</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:14\">2PE 3:14</a> <em>spotlessness</em></p>\n<h2>God promises to purify his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:25\">EZK 36:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:9\">ZEP 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:1\">ZEC 13:1</a></p>\n<h2>Purification through Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Through pardon offered in his death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Through his word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:3\">JHN 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:10\">JHN 13:10</a></p>\n<h3>Through his presence in resisting temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:7-Jas4:8\">JAS 4:7–4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:9\">1PE 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>Through hope built on his promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12-Titus2:13\">TIT 2:12–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:3\">1JN 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>Purification through judgment</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:28\">LEV 18:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:5\">DEU 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:7\">DEU 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:12\">DEU 17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:13\">JDG 20:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:2-Mal3:4\">MAL 3:2–3:4</a></p>\n<h3>In the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:13\">1CO 5:13</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Symbols of purity</h2>\n<h3>Whiteness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7\">PSA 51:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:18\">ISA 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:3\">MRK 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:3\">MAT 28:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5\">MRK 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:12\">JHN 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:14\">REV 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Light</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:5\">JOB 25:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:27\">EZK 1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14\">2CO 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:9\">EPH 5:8–5:9</a></p>\n<h3>Washing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:6\">PSA 26:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:2\">PSA 51:2</a></p>\n<h3>Fire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9-Dan7:10\">DAN 7:9–7:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:14\">ISA 33:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:2\">EZK 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:14-Rev1:15\">REV 1:14–1:15</a></p>",
